1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,030
There are awesome packages for data analysis in Python.

2
00:00:05,030 --> 00:00:10,720
A package is a collection of modules or python files that we can import into our code.

3
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:15,795
You can think of them as libraries of useful classes and functions that we can use.

4
00:00:15,794 --> 00:00:18,344
As a very simple example,

5
00:00:18,344 --> 00:00:21,029
let's say we wanted to find the mean of a list.

6
00:00:21,030 --> 00:00:23,280
We could code that manually by finding

7
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:26,745
the sum and dividing that by the length of the list.

8
00:00:26,745 --> 00:00:32,579
We could even create a function for it if we wanted to reuse it in multiple places.

9
00:00:32,579 --> 00:00:37,994
Or, we could just get this function from a library like Numpy.

10
00:00:37,994 --> 00:00:40,189
Here, we are importing the package.

11
00:00:40,189 --> 00:00:43,439
This is typically done at the beginning of your file.

12
00:00:43,439 --> 00:00:46,549
NP is the conventional alias for Numpy.

13
00:00:46,549 --> 00:00:50,494
Importing it without the alias is still valid but can quickly get annoying

14
00:00:50,494 --> 00:00:55,239
if you reference it a lot which will be the case for the packages we're using.

15
00:00:55,240 --> 00:00:59,155
Using a short alias helps keep your code concise and clean.

16
00:00:59,155 --> 00:01:02,240
Three powerful packages for data analysis that

17
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:06,210
we'll be using are Numpy, Pandas and Matplotlib.

18
00:01:06,209 --> 00:01:09,319
Numpy let's you perform mathematical functions on

19
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:13,169
large multi dimensional arrays and matrices efficiently.

20
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:16,310
Pandas is like a more powerful and flexible version

21
00:01:16,310 --> 00:01:19,545
of Excel that can handle large amounts of data.

22
00:01:19,545 --> 00:01:22,715
And, Matplotlib is a plotting library that can produce

23
00:01:22,715 --> 00:01:26,975
great visualizations often with very few lines of code.

24
00:01:26,974 --> 00:01:32,234
Links to documentation for these packages are provided in the instructor notes.

25
00:01:32,234 --> 00:01:34,980
Many people can be overwhelmed when they first try to navigate

26
00:01:34,980 --> 00:01:39,245
the docs to learn and master these packages, especially Pandas.

27
00:01:39,245 --> 00:01:43,490
We'll slowly introduce tools from each one throughout this course so that you can

28
00:01:43,489 --> 00:01:48,000
be comfortable using them and confident learning new things on your own with the docs.

